2. Various complications of pregnancy [14] 
 Ectopic pregnancy:  A condition where the fertilized egg implants outside your uterus (usually in Fallopian 
tube). This requires surgery or medication to remove the ectopic tissue.  
 Hyperemesis gravidarum (HG):  It is severe and persistent  vomiting during pregnancy. It can lead to
